<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Chargé in China (
                        Atcheson
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d986</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">986</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-03-29T15:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-03-29T15:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-29T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-29T15:00:00-05:00" n="986" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d986">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.4061 Motion Pictures/3–2945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-29T16:00:00-04:00">March 29, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>509. The Hays Organization<note n="2" xml:id="d986fn2">The Motion Picture
                        Producers and Distributors of America, Inc.</note> has informed the
                    Department of the receipt by its company members of advices from Chungking that
                    film remittances for 1945 (ReEmbs 2717 of June 26, 1944<note n="3" xml:id="d986fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1944v06#pg_1038">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1944, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">vi</hi>, p. 1038</ref>.</note>) will be computed on
                    a changed basis which will reduce substantially the net earnings of American
                    companies.</p>
                <p>The Hays Organization has requested the Embassy’s assistance in obtaining a more
                    reasonable arrangement in this matter and the Department would appreciate a
                    report in the premises by airgram indicating especially whether there was any
                    proper action which the Embassy was able to take in endeavoring to assist the
                    American companies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
